modules.description: Provides functions for asynchronous I/O operations, including reading from and writing to file descriptors, handling timeouts, and managing event loops. Works with Lwt's thread-based concurrency model and Unix-specific data types like file descriptors and time values. Enables non-blocking network communication and system call handling in real-time applications.

Provides route matching and handling using a list of route definitions. Operates on route structures that include HTTP methods, paths, and associated handlers. Used to build web applications with Lwt-based asynchronous request routing.
